review_text:
Posted: September 15
It's an interesting and challenging third-person action RPG with excellent combat and a great atmosphere. Many people have overly negative feelings about the game, thinking it's an absolute disaster. However, they miss the point that the game is trying something new instead of reusing the same formula. While it's not quite as good as the previous title, it's still fun and exciting. If you want an experience similar to the first game but not exactly the same, you won't be disappointed.

Pros:
- Great replayability;
- Awesome story and lore;
- Interesting new game+;
- Good art style and visuals;
- Fun and challenging gameplay;
- Wonderful soundtrack;
- Great optimization;
- Interesting multiplayer system;
- Good controls;
- Awesome boss fights;
- Great enemy variety;
- Memorable characters;
- Amazing level design;
- Great voice acting;

Cons:
- The DLCs are very hit-or-miss;
- Keyboard and mouse are not prompted;

Posted: February 10
this is the best souls like game you can play

if you can't play another souls likes :)

Posted: February 5
I always hated this game. It never felt really like dark souls to me, but i had never played it after scholar of the first sin was out. I'm now giving it a shot and it's pretty solid, even tho it has its defects.

Main bad stuff for me is:
- Adaptability feels so weird. I'd rather not have to level a status in order for my toon to drink faster and parry faster;
- The game feels slow, even slower than DS1;
- I feel like casting build are also slow, but i'm mainly a BOINKSTER so i could be wrong;
- The game won't feel too good until about the second half of the base content;
- Too many poison maps (mandatory on fromsoftware games, but this one outdid itself as to how many there are);
- Too many bonfires.

Pros:
- The lore is kinda nice;
- There's a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ of npcs you can round up at majula and their own lore is pretty warm and nice to know about;
- The variety of weapons and armor is astonishing;
- I feel like the map is so much bigger than DS1;
- To be completed once i finish all the DLC content.

By the tame of this review i'm finishing collecting the giant souls in order to slap Vendrick and killed all of the secondary bosses on the base game. Overall, if it's on sale, give it a try. The game is boring until you get to the second half, then it begins to improve. It's not as good as the other souls games, but it's still pretty nice. It's just the worse one among a series of really god-tier games. 7/10.
